/*Triangle, pentagonal, and hexagonal numbers are generated by the following formulae:

Triangle        Tn=n(n+1)/2     1, 3, 6, 10, 15, ...
Pentagonal      Pn=n(3n−1)/2        1, 5, 12, 22, 35, ...
Hexagonal       Hn=n(2n−1)      1, 6, 15, 28, 45, ...
It can be verified that T285 = P165 = H143 = 40755.

Find the next triangle number that is also pentagonal and hexagonal*/
public class Problem45 {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // TODO Auto-generated method stub

    }

    private static boolean isTriangle(int number) {
        return ((Math.sqrt(1 + 8 * number) -1 )/ 2) % 1 == 0;
    }
    
    private static boolean isPentagonal(int number) {
        return ((Math.sqrt(1 + 24 * number) +1 )/ 2) % 1 == 0;
    }
    
    private static boolean isHexagonal(int number) {
        return ((Math.sqrt(1 + 8 * number) +1 )/ 4) % 1 == 0;
    }
}
